# SynapseOS — Cursor Rules

You are building SynapseOS, a self-improving BYOK RAG platform on Oracle ARM (4 vCPU / 24GB RAM, NO GPU).

## Identity
- Project: SynapseOS — RAG platform with cognitive engine
- Repo: github.com/rahlplx/synapseos
- Owner: non-technical founder (vibe coder)
- Deploy target: Oracle ARM A1 via Coolify

## Locked Stack (never suggest alternatives to these)
- FastAPI 0.115 + Uvicorn | Python 3.11
- Qdrant 1.13.5 (hybrid: dense + sparse BM25 + RRF + cross-encoder)
- fastembed BAAI/bge-base-en-v1.5 (768d, ONNX, CPU-only)
- LiteLLM → Groq → OpenRouter → Anthropic (BYOK per tenant)
- mem0ai (Qdrant synapse_memory + PostgreSQL)
- Crawl4AI + Docling | RAGAS 0.2.15 | DSPy 2.5.20
- Langfuse v3 | KeyDB | MinIO | FastMCP 2.2.9
- Cloudflare Workers edge cache

## ARM Hard Rules
- OMP_NUM_THREADS=4 in every file using ONNX
- batch_size=64 ingestion, batch_size=16 query
- Cross-encoder input cap = 15 docs max
- KeyDB: appendonly yes, save "" (NO RDB — fork causes OOM)
- Qdrant: on_disk=True, memmap_threshold_kb=50000
- Docling: concurrency=1, DOCLING_CPU_ONLY=1
- Max RAM budget: 24GB total, FastAPI gets 6GB max

## Code Style
- Always async/await — no sync blocking calls in FastAPI routes
- All secrets via os.environ — never hardcoded
- Complete files only — no partial code, no ellipsis, no "# add rest here"
- All imports at top of file
- Type hints on all functions
- Fernet AES-256 for encrypting tenant BYOK keys in PostgreSQL
- tenant_id filter on every Qdrant query — no cross-tenant data leakage

## Collections
- synapse_knowledge → RAG document vectors
- synapse_memory → mem0 long-term memory vectors

## LLM Routing (never change this)
- Generation: groq/llama-3.1-70b-versatile
- Fast tasks (classify/reflect): groq/llama-3.1-8b-instant
- Fallback chain: Groq → OpenRouter → Anthropic

## What NOT to Do
- Never suggest z.ai API in runtime code
- Never use sync database calls in async routes
- Never put secrets in docker-compose.yml directly
- Never use RDB snapshots in KeyDB config
- Never embed more than batch_size=64 at once during ingestion
- Never pass more than 15 docs to cross-encoder
- Never use Celery (too heavy — use KeyDB job queue + BackgroundTasks)
- Never suggest GPU-dependent libraries
